This paper is primarily focused on visual localization, which is a topic in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new neural network architecture for predicting scene coordinates, which involves both classification and regression tasks. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.RO (Robotics), which often involve the use of machine learning techniques. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which is a topic in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several datasets, which may be relevant to sub-category cs.GR (Graphics).
